Nice, but could use some more detail.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
The reason why this works is that you are naming the sp parameters the exactly the same, and when you create the data sets based on those sps bids creates the parameters for you.  you can, however, achieve the exact same thing without having to have the sp parameters be spelled exactly the same.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
under the dataset properties under the parameters tab, you can assigned a report parameter to a stored procedure parameter, no matter the spelling.&lt;br /&gt;
